<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
    
    <body>

        <h1>What Can JavaScript Do?</h1>

        <p>JavaScript can change HTML attributes.</p>

        <p>In this case JavaScript changes the src (source) attribute of an image. <br>Give it a shot!  Are you happy or sad?</p>

<button onclick="document.getElementById('Emotion').src='pic_happy.png'">Happy</button>

<img id="Emotion" src="pic_happy.png" style="width:203px">

<button onclick="document.getElementById('Emotion').src='pic_sad.png'">Sad</button>

    </body>
    
</html>
